A class contains all of the journal entry details for each transaction (e.g. associated journal entry ID, associated account number, debits or credits associated with the journal entry line). This table should be at the journal entry line level.
ID
The unique identifier for a journal entry.
Number
The number for each journal entry in a financial recording system.
Effective Date
The date that officially recognizes the journal entry within an entity's financial accounting records, irrespective of the actual entry creation or receipt date.
Description
The text that characterizes the overall journal entry.
Activities
A class capturing a record of system user actions within an auditee's system, which includes instances of entry, approval, last modification, and posting of data or transactions.
(Approved) Activity
A class that records specific actions or tasks completed or in progress.
Date
The date marks when an activity occurred, ideally recorded automatically by the system.
Time
The specified time at which an activity occurs.
User
The reference association to the User class, which is a class with user details, important for overseeing access, maintaining security, and tracking system use.
ID
The reference identifier for individuals entering transactions into the accounting and/or ERP system.

Accounting Period

A specific duration within a fiscal year, delineated by its beginning and ending dates. It serves as the timeframe during which business transactions and entries are accumulated and organized into financial statements and reports.
Fiscal Year
The year for which financial records are kept, expressed in four digits.
ID
The span of time covered by an accounting record.
General Ledger Source

The reference association to the General Ledger Source class, which is a class details the origins of data in the General Ledger Journal Entry, including the ERP systems or accounting packages involved and the related business processes.
Code
The unique code indicating the origin of a journal entry.
Journal Entry Type
The reference association to the Journal Entry Type class, which is a class details the types of journal entries in the General Ledger such as cash receipts and cash disbursements.
Code
The unique code specifying the type of journal entry.
JP Journal Entry Line

A class contains all of the journal entry line details for each transaction (e.g. associated journal entry ID, associated account number, debits or credits associated with the journal entry line). This table should be at the journal entry line level.
Journal ID
Unique identifier for each journal entry line.
Number
The number for a line within a journal entry.
Description
The text that characterizes a line within a journal entry.
Reversal Indicator
A code that indicates if a general ledger entry line is a reversal or is to be reversed.
Reversal Journal ID
The Journal ID of the journal entry line that corresponds to the original entry line being reversed if the Reversal Indicator is set.
Cancellation Indicator
Signifies whether a journal entry line, already formed but not yet posted, has been cancelled or not.
(Unit Price) Amount
A class that specifies a value of money in a given currency.
Value
The numerical value representing a sum of money.
Currency
The reference association to the Currency class, which is a class holds information about different currencies.
Code
The official name of the currency utilized in the accounting and/or ERP system.
Bill
A class of document that is officially cited within another record or transaction, serving as verification or supporting detail for financial or operational activities.
ID
The unique identifier for the referenced document.
Date
The date associated with a business transaction.
Bill Type

The reference association to the Bill Type class, which is a class describes the category of a bill such as bank draft or check, often used in business transactions as evidence of debt or payment instruments.
Code
The unique code that classifies the type of bill.
Quantity
A class that measures the extent, size, or amount of items, including the unit of measurement.
Value
The numerical amount of a specified item or resource.
Measurement Unit
The reference association to the Measurement Unit class, which is a class documents the units of measure utilized across various business documents and accounting ledgers.
UOM Code
The unique code for the unit of measure used in transactions.
(Account Segment) Bank Account
The reference association to the Account Segment Bank Account class, which is a class includes details associated with a bank account.
Number
The unique number for an account within a financial institution, for which the use of ISO 13616-2 International Bank Account Number (IBAN) format is recommended when applicable.
(Account Segment) Employee
The reference association to the Account Segment Employee class, which is a class that holds individual employee details within a specific accounting entity.
ID
The reference identifier for an employee.
(Account Segment) Project

The reference association to the Account Segment Project class, which is a class designed for specific projects that can vary from construction to research and may receive public or private funding. It methodically logs key information such as organizational hierarchy, strategic approaches, processes, steps taken, records, budgetary outlines, actual expenses, and the progress made toward set goals.
ID
The reference identifier for a project.
Settlement Method

The reference association to the Settlement Method class, which is a class describing various methodologies adopted by the business to settle transactions, which can range from cash payments to bank transfers.
Code
The unique code describing how a transaction is settled.
(Debit) JP Ledger Account
A class stores information about General Ledger accounts.
Account Number
The unique identifier assigned to a general ledger account, categorically coded to align with established accounting principles and the specific characteristics of the business.
Account Name
The official title assigned to a general ledger account that uniquely identifies it within an accounting framework.
Description
The descriptive label or text providing additional details about a general ledger account that corresponds to the General Ledger Account Number.
Financial Statement Caption

The label utilized within financial statements to aggregate and present related financial account details, facilitating the organization and understanding of a company's financial data as reported in its financial statements.
Account Type
The classification of an account reflecting its nature and purpose.
Account Subtype
The classification detailing a more specific categorization within an account type.
Account Hierarchy
The class representing the structured levels of account classification within an organization's accounting system.
Balance Debit Or Credit Code
The classification identifying the natural balance of an account, denoted by 'D' for a debit balance, or 'C' for a credit balance.
Subsidiary Ledger Account

A class for an account within a subsidiary ledger that holds transaction details specific to a particular customer, vendor, asset, or other individual entity. Each account is associated with a unique subsidiary account number and corresponding details in the general ledger. The ledger serves as a detailed companion to the general ledger for managing detailed accounting transactions.
Subsidiary Item Number
The number of subsidiary item
Subsidiary Item Name
The name of subsidiary item
Code List Name

The data file that is linked to and provides detailed information relevant to The specific subsidiary item. Each file contains records pertinent to its associated entity, facilitating the management and retrieval of entity-specific data within the subsidiary ledger system.
Description of Code List Name
The detailed description of subsidiary item

JP Tax Type

A class that has been updated to comply with the reporting requirements of the Japanese Tax Agency for consumption tax. This includes the inclusion of the tax category code to enhance specificity and adherence to regulatory standards.

Description

Tax Code Description

Tax Percentage
The standard rate applied to a specific tax type and code.
